WEBVTT

00:04.804 --> 00:08.174
<i>[light, echoing music]</i>

00:08.241 --> 00:10.577
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:10.677 --> 00:13.179
<i>narrator: Since learning</i>
<i>of Becca's pregnancy</i>

00:13.246 --> 00:16.750
<i>as well as his own lack</i>
<i>of agency in relation to it,</i>

00:16.850 --> 00:20.420
<i>Marcus had tried</i>
<i>to go about his life as usual</i>

00:20.520 --> 00:22.756
<i>to control</i>
<i>the things he could.</i>

00:22.856 --> 00:25.759
<i>[ambient music]</i>

00:25.859 --> 00:32.599
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:33.767 --> 00:35.602
- Marcus, you okay?

00:36.536 --> 00:37.570
- Oh, uh--

00:37.670 --> 00:38.838
uh, yes, yeah.

00:38.905 --> 00:40.240
Um...

00:40.340 --> 00:43.076
could you print out Trey Lane's
new pages for me?

00:43.176 --> 00:44.778
And, um...

00:44.878 --> 00:47.680
could I also get a tea
with honey and lemon?

00:47.747 --> 00:49.783
- Oh, the hot water thing's
broken.

00:49.883 --> 00:51.618
- Fine, uh, coffee.

00:51.718 --> 00:54.587
- The coffee thing's connected
to the hot water thing.

00:55.789 --> 00:58.191
- Go to a coffee shop then.

00:58.258 --> 00:59.392
- Okay.

00:59.459 --> 01:01.928
Wait,
do you want the tea again?

01:02.028 --> 01:03.730
Or would--
- I, uh--

01:06.699 --> 01:09.369
<i>[energetic music]</i>

01:09.436 --> 01:10.770
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:10.870 --> 01:12.906
<i>narrator:</i>
<i>But everywhere he turned,</i>

01:12.972 --> 01:17.043
<i>Marcus was hard-pressed to</i>
<i>find even a shred of evidence</i>

01:17.110 --> 01:19.112
<i>that he was</i>
<i>in the driver's seat</i>

01:19.212 --> 01:20.947
<i>of his own life.</i>

01:21.047 --> 01:23.950
<i>[lively music]</i>

01:24.050 --> 01:25.618
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:25.718 --> 01:27.153
<i>Even his own thoughts</i>

01:27.253 --> 01:29.322
<i>seemed to have</i>
<i>a life of their own,</i>

01:29.422 --> 01:32.125
<i>playing and endless game</i>
<i>of "What if?"</i>

01:32.225 --> 01:34.160
<i>What if he'd never met Becca?</i>

01:34.260 --> 01:36.830
<i>What if he'd never had</i>
<i>that threesome?</i>

01:36.930 --> 01:39.632
<i>What if he'd just</i>
<i>worn a condom?</i>

01:39.732 --> 01:42.502
<i>What if he just disappeared?</i>

01:42.602 --> 01:45.772
<i>Better yet,</i>
<i>what if Becca disappeared?</i>

01:45.839 --> 01:47.807
<i>A carbon monoxide leak.</i>

01:47.907 --> 01:50.009
<i>A piano falling from the sky.</i>

01:50.110 --> 01:52.412
<i>Something quick and painless,</i>
<i>of course.</i>

01:52.479 --> 01:54.681
<i>He wasn't a monster.</i>

01:54.781 --> 01:56.182
<i>Or maybe he was.</i>

01:56.282 --> 01:58.351
<i>Maybe he was just another</i>
<i>awful man</i>

01:58.451 --> 02:00.453
<i>trying to weasel</i>
<i>out of the consequences</i>

02:00.520 --> 02:02.455
<i>of his own actions.</i>

02:03.590 --> 02:06.192
- You can't hide in here
forever.

02:06.926 --> 02:08.528
- I don't want to have a baby.

02:08.628 --> 02:10.330
- And I don't want
to be in love with the ex

02:10.430 --> 02:13.032
who cut half my dreads off
in my sleep one time.

02:13.133 --> 02:15.268
But life throws shit at ya.

02:15.335 --> 02:16.769
- So your parents never,
I guess,

02:16.836 --> 02:18.671
told you about the birds
and the bees and shit.

02:18.771 --> 02:20.106
Okay, so, like,
you have the--

02:20.173 --> 02:22.041
okay you have--
for you it's this, right?

02:22.142 --> 02:24.644
And you put the condom over it
and<i> then</i> you have sex.

02:24.711 --> 02:25.879
And that way...

02:25.979 --> 02:27.180
- Ki-Kian--
- babies don't happen.

02:27.280 --> 02:28.548
- Look,
after that last breakup,

02:28.648 --> 02:30.049
I went through
a string of women.

02:30.150 --> 02:31.885
- Yeah, but did you
get any of them pregnant?

02:31.985 --> 02:35.321
- I was gonna do IVF
with Nicole.

02:35.388 --> 02:36.956
But that would have been
a huge mistake.

02:37.023 --> 02:38.691
- Oh, my God.
- That would've been horrible.

02:38.791 --> 02:41.227
- But listen man,
you're about to have a kid

02:41.327 --> 02:42.695
that's gonna be literally,
like,

02:42.795 --> 02:44.364
genetically coded
to accept you.

02:44.464 --> 02:45.798
That's cool.
- Right.

02:45.865 --> 02:47.534
Because nobody hates
their parents, right?

02:47.634 --> 02:49.802
- Oh, I'm just trying to
look on the bright side, man.

02:49.869 --> 02:53.173
Seriously, maybe this will
bring you and this Becca chick

02:53.239 --> 02:54.507
closer together.

02:54.574 --> 02:56.743
I mean,
it's fucking rough out there.

02:56.843 --> 02:58.845
You know,
I can't find anyone to love me.

02:58.912 --> 03:00.413
- [chuckles]
- Seriously.

03:00.513 --> 03:02.048
At first, I was kinda like,

03:02.148 --> 03:04.717
"I don't want a woman to love
me because of my money."

03:04.817 --> 03:07.854
And now, I'm like, "Fine,
love me because of my money."

03:08.721 --> 03:10.156
Love me for something,
you know?

03:11.090 --> 03:12.258
- Shit, Kian, I'm sorry.

03:12.358 --> 03:13.526
- No, no, no, no, no,
it's fine.

03:13.593 --> 03:15.228
It's all right.
It's cool.

03:15.328 --> 03:17.263
- I still have some IVF
in the freezer.

03:17.363 --> 03:18.765
Can you see me with a baby?

03:18.865 --> 03:20.433
[chuckles]

03:20.533 --> 03:23.269
But come to think of it...

03:23.369 --> 03:25.004
your baby would have had
a cousin.

03:26.105 --> 03:28.274
- Yo, what is this?

03:28.374 --> 03:29.943
MSG change the dress code?

03:30.043 --> 03:31.044
Look at yourself.

03:31.110 --> 03:33.346
- Nah, nah, bro.
Not quite.

03:33.413 --> 03:35.515
You are looking at
front office Yogi now.

03:35.582 --> 03:36.616
- [laughs]
Man,

03:36.716 --> 03:38.451
that's what I'm talking about.

03:38.551 --> 03:40.753
You made the leap.
I'm so proud of you.

03:40.853 --> 03:42.789
- I'm glad somebody is.
Tina saw my check

03:42.889 --> 03:44.757
and couldn't even look me
in the face for like a week.

03:44.857 --> 03:47.393
She was like,
"Damn, assistant pay!"

03:47.460 --> 03:48.728
It's cool though, man.

03:48.795 --> 03:50.129
This is about the future,
though, you know?

03:50.230 --> 03:51.431
Trying to set it up, man.

03:51.531 --> 03:52.932
Sometimes you gotta play
the long game.

03:53.032 --> 03:54.467
- Exactly, exactly.
She'll come around, man.

03:54.567 --> 03:55.969
- Oh yeah, yeah, I don't
even worry about that.

03:56.069 --> 03:57.303
I don't worry about that,
bro.

03:57.403 --> 03:59.138
But you know,
if I hadn't had my kids,

03:59.239 --> 04:01.741
I would literally be cool,
just, you know,

04:01.808 --> 04:04.210
hanging out,
being where I was at.

04:04.277 --> 04:07.213
Drinking a beer
with a dumb-ass sweatshirt on

04:07.280 --> 04:08.481
looking stupid.
- All right, all right.

04:08.581 --> 04:10.049
- Ha!
Hear me out. Hear me out.

04:10.116 --> 04:12.485
I'm not trying to lecture you.
Okay? I'm not.

04:12.585 --> 04:14.487
But it's like, bro--

04:14.587 --> 04:17.423
Like, I love my kids, man.
You know I do.

04:17.490 --> 04:18.992
Like, they really inspire me,
man.

04:19.092 --> 04:20.994
They're in the car right now
with the window cracked.

04:21.094 --> 04:22.662
They're fine, they're fine.
It's the--

04:22.762 --> 04:24.497
wait, is that for kidnappers
or dogs?

04:24.597 --> 04:26.299
- No, you leave
the window cracked for dogs.

04:26.399 --> 04:27.900
You're not supposed to leave
your kids in the car at all.

04:27.967 --> 04:30.103
I thought, but--
- No, if you turn the car off

04:30.169 --> 04:31.938
and leave the radio on--
like, leave it on ACC,

04:32.005 --> 04:33.406
I think you're fine.
Anyway, the point

04:33.473 --> 04:35.341
I'm trying to make, bro,
is that they inspire me.

04:35.441 --> 04:37.443
I wouldn't be who I am
without them, bro.

04:37.510 --> 04:40.480
Like,
you cannot tap out right now.

04:40.580 --> 04:42.515
You gotta
see this shit through.

04:42.615 --> 04:44.284
- But look, man,
I mean, I--

04:44.350 --> 04:47.186
Becca already has two kids.
She doesn't need me.

04:47.287 --> 04:49.622
- Bro, that might be the most
deadbeat as deadbeat shit

04:49.689 --> 04:51.190
I ever heard in my life.
What are you talking about?

04:51.291 --> 04:52.358
- No, no, no, it's not--

04:52.458 --> 04:53.660
- Come on, man.

04:53.760 --> 04:55.194
You gotta be there
for this kid, bro.

04:55.295 --> 04:56.829
The stakes
are a little different for us.

04:56.929 --> 04:58.331
The kid's gonna be Black.

04:58.431 --> 04:59.999
It's a big deal.
You understand me?

05:00.099 --> 05:01.634
He can't be around
these hedge fund motherfuckers

05:01.701 --> 05:03.002
and these bankers.
They gonna have

05:03.102 --> 05:04.370
this motherfucker
watching "The Help"

05:04.470 --> 05:05.938
to find out
what it's like to be

05:06.005 --> 05:07.373
a Black man in America.
Is that what you want?

05:07.473 --> 05:09.108
- This is why I tried to have,
like,

05:09.175 --> 05:10.877
a real-ass conversation
with Becca.

05:10.977 --> 05:13.346
- This is why you can't try,
though, you have to just do it.

05:13.446 --> 05:15.648
- You gotta mold this kid.
It's gonna look like you.

05:15.715 --> 05:17.317
It needs to act like you.

05:17.383 --> 05:20.219
Come on, man, you a great dude.
You got a lot to offer.

05:20.320 --> 05:23.456
This kid is gonna be excited
to have a dad like you.

05:23.523 --> 05:25.191
Plus,
the whole fatherhood shit--

05:25.291 --> 05:26.959
this is, like--
that's where you get, like,

05:27.026 --> 05:28.828
your man badge at.
This is, like--

05:28.895 --> 05:31.064
this is where you earn it, bro.

05:31.164 --> 05:32.865
What kind of man
do you want to be?

05:34.133 --> 05:36.302
Hm?
[car honking]

05:36.369 --> 05:38.004
Oh, shit, wait,
that's my kids.

05:38.071 --> 05:40.006
All right, I gotta go, man.
I'm double-parked.

05:40.073 --> 05:41.474
I hope I got through to you,
bro.

05:41.541 --> 05:43.509
Clean this shit up,
and I'm not playing.

05:43.576 --> 05:44.644
All right?

05:44.711 --> 05:46.479
And shave too.
You look stupid.

05:46.546 --> 05:47.580
- [laughs]

05:47.680 --> 05:48.881
[door clicks open]

05:51.751 --> 05:52.719
[door clicks shut]

05:52.819 --> 05:55.221
<i>[pensive music]</i>

05:56.089 --> 05:57.490
<i>narrator: In a split second,</i>

05:57.557 --> 06:00.259
<i>Marcus' life</i>
<i>had taken a sharp turn.</i>

06:01.094 --> 06:05.698
<i>And for the first time ever,</i>
<i>he simply gave in,</i>

06:05.765 --> 06:07.734
<i>as messy as it was.</i>

06:07.834 --> 06:08.935
<i>- Hello?</i>

06:11.371 --> 06:12.438
- Hi.

06:13.506 --> 06:15.608
Hi, it's Marcus.

06:15.708 --> 06:17.176
<i>- I know who it is.</i>

06:17.243 --> 06:18.945
<i>It's been a while.</i>

06:19.045 --> 06:20.246
- Yeah.

06:22.615 --> 06:24.016
How are you doing?

06:25.418 --> 06:26.953
<i>- I'm doing okay.</i>

06:27.053 --> 06:30.790
<i>[light, emotional music]</i>

06:30.890 --> 06:37.730
<i>♪ ♪</i>

06:37.797 --> 06:39.265
- Marcus.

06:40.233 --> 06:41.234
- Becca, hey.

06:41.300 --> 06:43.269
Uh, wow, you look--

06:43.369 --> 06:44.537
uh...

06:44.604 --> 06:46.472
- Like a soccer mom
in distress?

06:46.572 --> 06:47.974
[laughs]
- No, no, no.

06:48.074 --> 06:49.776
I was gonna say, uh--
- [clears throat]

06:49.876 --> 06:52.912
- You look very normal and--

06:52.979 --> 06:54.881
and healthy.
- Hmm.

06:54.947 --> 06:57.617
That's the nicest thing
you've said to me in a month.

06:59.886 --> 07:01.621
- Becca Evans.

07:03.723 --> 07:05.491
- [clears throat]
Hi.

07:05.591 --> 07:08.594
- Here's the questionnaire
for the genetic counseling.

07:08.661 --> 07:10.062
- Thank you.

07:10.129 --> 07:11.564
Um, he needs one too.

07:12.665 --> 07:13.666
- Oh, hi, yeah.

07:13.766 --> 07:16.002
I'm, uh, the other parent.

07:16.102 --> 07:18.838
- Oh, of course you are.

07:23.609 --> 07:25.178
- "Oh, of course you are."

07:25.278 --> 07:28.314
What the fuck was that?
- It--it's--it's fine.

07:28.414 --> 07:31.184
- Well, I don't know who should
be more insulted, you or me.

07:31.284 --> 07:33.319
- Well,
I'm pretty sure it's me,

07:33.419 --> 07:35.021
but it seems like it's you.

07:35.121 --> 07:36.522
- Fucking bitch.

07:41.360 --> 07:43.196
Thank you for coming.

07:43.296 --> 07:45.965
I'm actually relieved
not to be doing this alone.

07:46.966 --> 07:49.268
- No, I mean, no, it's--

07:49.335 --> 07:50.670
it's good for me too.

07:52.638 --> 07:54.507
- Every woman carries the risk
of having a baby

07:54.607 --> 07:56.976
with chromosomal abnormality
or genetic issues,

07:57.043 --> 08:00.480
but as we know, the risk
increases with maternal age.

08:00.546 --> 08:03.382
Um, paternal genetics
can affect this too.

08:03.483 --> 08:05.051
So...

08:05.151 --> 08:06.819
Looks like you skipped a few.

08:06.886 --> 08:08.488
What about Tay-Sachs,
does that ring a bell?

08:08.554 --> 08:10.389
Do you have any
Jewish ancestry?

08:10.490 --> 08:12.325
- Um, uh, no.

08:13.526 --> 08:15.027
- Right, of course not.

08:15.962 --> 08:17.697
What about cystic fibrosis?

08:17.797 --> 08:18.898
- Uh,

08:18.998 --> 08:21.534
I'm not sure
about that one either,

08:21.634 --> 08:22.735
but I don't--
I don't think so.

08:22.835 --> 08:23.870
- Well, can you find out?

08:23.970 --> 08:25.571
- Oh, yeah, sure.
I'll ask my mom.

08:29.008 --> 08:30.409
Oh, you want me to ask
right now.

08:30.510 --> 08:32.578
- It certainly would
speed up the process.

08:32.678 --> 08:33.713
- Yeah, yeah, sure.

08:33.813 --> 08:34.914
Um...

08:35.748 --> 08:37.183
I feel like I should have
gotten an email

08:37.250 --> 08:39.585
with this questionnaire
in advance.

08:39.685 --> 08:42.655
[line ringing]

08:42.722 --> 08:44.490
<i>[hip-hop music playing]</i>
- Yo.

08:44.557 --> 08:46.158
- Hey, sis, quick question--

08:46.225 --> 08:47.426
<i>what did Uncle Harry die of?</i>

08:47.527 --> 08:49.095
<i>Was that cystic fibrosis?</i>

08:49.195 --> 08:50.596
<i>♪ ♪</i>

08:50.696 --> 08:51.864
- What?

08:51.931 --> 08:54.066
- Um,
I'm at the OB-GYN with Becca.

08:54.166 --> 08:56.435
- Oh, that is really sweet.

08:56.536 --> 08:57.603
Have a good time, Marcus.

08:57.703 --> 08:59.105
- No, no, no, no.
Wait, wait, wait.

08:59.205 --> 09:00.606
What about Uncle Henry?

09:00.706 --> 09:02.441
- Fool, I don't know
how that old bastard died.

09:02.542 --> 09:04.110
Call Mom. I'm busy.

09:05.044 --> 09:06.512
- [sighs]

09:06.579 --> 09:08.781
<i>- Okay,</i>
<i>so you want to be a dad,</i>

09:08.881 --> 09:11.250
but you don't want anyone
to know about the kid.

09:11.350 --> 09:12.785
[laughs]

09:12.885 --> 09:15.054
You sound like Drake 2.0.
I'm telling you.

09:15.121 --> 09:18.724
- Well, I will tell them
when the time is right.

09:18.791 --> 09:20.593
- Uh-huh.
Listen, Marcus,

09:20.693 --> 09:23.129
I don't know anything
about our family history, okay?

09:23.229 --> 09:26.032
So just, I don't know,
make something up.

09:26.098 --> 09:27.433
<i>♪ ♪</i>

09:29.035 --> 09:30.136
- [sighs]

09:32.104 --> 09:33.639
No history of it.

09:37.109 --> 09:38.444
You live up here, huh?

09:38.544 --> 09:39.545
- Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah.

09:39.612 --> 09:41.414
Just a few blocks up that way.

09:41.480 --> 09:43.082
- Oh.

09:43.149 --> 09:44.951
- You've never been
to my place, have you?

09:45.051 --> 09:47.486
- No I--I honestly thought
you lived at the Palace Hotel.

09:47.587 --> 09:48.754
- [laughs]

09:48.821 --> 09:51.557
Do you--
do you wanna come see it?

09:51.624 --> 09:54.093
I make a mean cocktail.

09:54.160 --> 09:56.329
For you, not for me.
- I know.

09:56.429 --> 09:57.897
Anyway, you should probably
see where you're gonna be

09:57.964 --> 09:59.498
picking this kid up from
on weekends.

09:59.599 --> 10:01.934
- Oh, already jumping into
the custody conversation.

10:02.001 --> 10:03.302
Cool, cool, cool, cool.

10:03.402 --> 10:05.271
- Ugh, I'm a planner.
What can I say?

10:05.338 --> 10:06.472
- Yeah, clearly.

10:06.572 --> 10:08.307
- Asshole. Come on.
- [laughs]

10:08.407 --> 10:09.442
- Such an asshole.

10:09.508 --> 10:12.011
[liquid pouring]

10:14.580 --> 10:17.149
- I promise we are going to

10:17.249 --> 10:20.653
baby-proof the shit
out of this place.

10:20.753 --> 10:22.855
I mean, I don't know.
I might even move.

10:22.955 --> 10:24.156
- What?

10:24.256 --> 10:25.992
And deprive the kid
of this view?

10:26.092 --> 10:28.995
- I don't know, just trying
to make the best of my do-over.

10:29.095 --> 10:30.496
Cheers?
[door thuds shut]

10:30.596 --> 10:33.165
[footsteps approaching]

10:33.265 --> 10:34.700
- Oh, God, Mom.

10:34.800 --> 10:36.202
Is this the guy?

10:36.302 --> 10:37.803
- This is Marcus.

10:37.870 --> 10:40.373
- You literally said
we'd never have to meet him.

10:40.473 --> 10:42.608
Do we have any food?
I'm fucking starving

10:42.675 --> 10:44.710
and the animal shelter
only has shitty snacks.

10:44.810 --> 10:46.212
- It's community service,
Maddie,

10:46.312 --> 10:47.680
not an all-inclusive resort.

10:47.780 --> 10:49.882
- Well,
I feel like a fucking prisoner.

10:49.982 --> 10:52.284
- Maddie got a DUI after
swerving onto a lawn

10:52.351 --> 10:53.786
and hitting a mini Labradoodle.

10:53.853 --> 10:55.154
- Oh.
- Shut up, Mom!

10:55.221 --> 10:57.556
- Hey!
I know you're angry, Maddie.

10:57.657 --> 10:59.458
But I am not the enemy here.

11:00.393 --> 11:01.894
I'm so sorry
you had to see that.

11:01.994 --> 11:03.195
I just--I don't know

11:03.295 --> 11:05.231
where she gets
that attitude from.

11:05.331 --> 11:07.566
- Oh, well,
it's from her dad, right?

11:07.667 --> 11:09.735
It obviously can't be from you.

11:09.835 --> 11:12.071
- Yeah.
[both laugh]

11:13.039 --> 11:14.674
- I don't know.
She splits her time

11:14.740 --> 11:17.743
between here with me
and Connecticut with him.

11:17.843 --> 11:20.913
And he just lets her run wild
as, like, a "fuck you" to me.

11:21.013 --> 11:24.316
And they break your heart
every day.

11:24.383 --> 11:26.218
But she'll always
be my little baby.

11:26.318 --> 11:27.353
